_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Star Wars\u2019 next animated anthology explores the dark side", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-04T18:16:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Disney Plus logo on a black and red background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hahQwIwyGbVs1WSrgNgApBCqGf4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73256063/acastro_STK080_disneyPlus_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"oUaFVs\">Disney Plus already has rules in place to prevent subscribers from sharing their passwords \u2014 but now we have an idea when it will start making users pay to share them. In <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/video/2024/04/04/disney-ceo-bob-iger-on-streaming-we-have-to-turn-it-into-a-growth-business.html\">an interview on CNBC</a>, Disney CEO Bob Iger says the company plans on \u201claunching our first real foray into password sharing\u201d in June.</p>\n<p id=\"4vMjLI\">Iger says the rollout will start in \u201cjust a few countries in a few markets\u201d before expanding to all subscribers in September. Disney\u2019s anti-password sharing rules initially <a href=\"http", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/4/24121189/disney-plus-paid-password-sharing-crackdown-june", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Disney Plus password-sharing crackdown starts in June", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-04T17:20:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Tesla logo stock\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sd9RGHIXn8xhbgc1LRTzL4slJ2c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73255881/tesla.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"J4zqzp\">Tesla is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/11/24097480/tesla-walter-huang-crash-lawsuit-court-autopilot\">going to court next week</a> over the role its Autopilot system played in a fatal crash in 2018 \u2014 and it wants Apple to testify in its defense. </p>\n<p id=\"BO5GGx\">Tesla wants to prove that Apple engineer Wei \u201cWalter\u201d Huang was playing a video game on his phone at the time his Autopilot-enabled Model X smashed into a safety barrier along US Highway 101 in Mountain View, California, in 2018. And now, Huang\u2019s family, which is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/5/1/18525330/tesla-autopilot-lawsuit-model-x-crash-walter-huang\">suing Tesla for wrongful death</a>, is claiming th", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/4/24121014/tesla-apple-huang-autopilot-wrongful-death-trial", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tesla is dragging Apple into its upcoming fatal Autopilot crash trial", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-04T17:10:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of Paul Sun-Hyung Lee.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5gM1UcspZU8Z81HHFiSlTiTRxT0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73255855/247072__Paul_Sun_Hyung_Lee_CVirginia_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photo by Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>As Paul Sun-Hyung Lee sees it, truly loving a genre franchise means wanting to share it and pass it along to the next generation of fans.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24118292/paul-sun-hyung-lee-avatar-mandalorian-ahsoka-interview\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24118292/paul-sun-hyung-lee-avatar-mandalorian-ahsoka-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Avatar\u2019s Paul Sun-Hyung Lee wants to geek out with the fans of the future", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-04T15:46:16+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A pile of five Pixel 8 devices.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CCKdPoJemfnggTYFZ7ZR585keC0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73255576/236823_Pixel_8_8Pro_Watch2_VPavic_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NjlhUX\">The launch of Google\u2019s long-awaited Find My Device network is seemingly almost here. In <a href=\"https://9to5google.com/2024/04/04/google-android-find-my-device-network-launch-date\">an email spotted by <em>9to5Google</em></a>, Google tells users it will turn on the feature in three days, which uses data from millions of other Android devices to find the location of missing phones and accessories \u2014 similar to the tracking tech <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/22/22396693/apple-airtag-location-tracker-hands-on-find-my-privacy-safety\">used by Apple</a> and Tile.</p>\n<p id=\"GbyiHq\">The email says users can use the network to \u201cfind any compa", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/4/24120984/google-find-my-device-network-launch-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s expanded Find My Device network might arrive in a few days", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-04T15:03:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Close-up of the Garmin HRM-Fit\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/J-HKCnJg7GUT6eFEh7jSNY_6Oe4=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73255396/247020_Garmin_HRM_Fit_AKrales_0012.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Finally, a chest strap that doesn\u2019t make me feel like a python is crushing my ribs.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Finally, a chest strap that works with my sports bra \u2014 not against it.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24119970/garmin-hrm-fit-review-chest-strap-wearables-fitness\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24119970/garmin-hrm-fit-review-chest-strap-wearables-fitness", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Garmin\u2019s new heart rate tracker pairs nearly perfectly with sports bras", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked"