ollowers. </p>\n<p id=\"JkwvrS\">Multiple X users on Wednesday reported seeing the familiar blue \u201cVerified\u201d checkmark next to their handles despite not paying for either paid X subscription tier. Musk last week <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/27/24114185/elon-musk-has-a-new-pay-to-play-x-premium-gambit\">announced</a> that X accounts with over 2,500 \u201cverified subscriber followers\u201d would receive ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/3/24120602/x-free-premium-verified-blue-checkmark", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "X\u2019s \u2018complimentary\u2019 Premium push gives people blue checks they didn\u2019t ask for", "user": null, "vote": 0}]